						<summary>

						<p>This is made up of two separate pieces found engraved on different slabs built into the right and left sides of the entrance. It records a gift of ten <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of Vāḷaiyūr for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tāntōṉṟipperumāḷ by one Vaḍugaṉ Kāḷaiyaṉ Āchchaṉ. </p>						

